  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In April and May 2015, two major earthquakes in Nepal killed nearly 8,000 people, injured 10,000, and affected 8 million across the country. The Global Fund for Children is mobilizing funds to support five grassroots organizations that are bringing emergency relief and ongoing support to vulnerable Nepalese children and their families. As trusted community resources, these organizations are uniquely positioned to identify and fulfill critical needs.</narrative>
